properties.documentation: QualityElement shall be described with elements defined in clauses 8.3.2 through to 8.3.7 of this standard, or a combination of these. In case elements defined in this standard are not sufficient for expressing the quality of the dataset, new elements can be defined according to the requirements specified in Clause 8.4. See Permission 1
In case additional quality elements have been defined for QualityElement in compliance of Clause 8.4 of this standard, these can be used to describe that QualityElement

New quality element shall be defined as a specialisation of QualityElement, (see Clause 8.3) in compliance with the rules for metadata extensions (ISO 19115-1:2014, Annex C) and rules for domain profiles of standard schemas (ISO 19109:2015, Clause 8.3). NOTE 1: If applicable, elements defined in other standards (e.g. ISO/IEC 25000 series) can be used for extending the set of quality components as defined in Clause 8.
If Completeness is reported as data quality information, it shall be defined by one or more of these elements: Commission and Omission.
Data quality evaluation method shall be included for each applied data quality measure.
One date or range of dates (compliant with ISO 19108) should be included for each evaluation. If the evaluation was carried out on non-consecutive dates, each single date should be included.

If LogicalConsistency is reported as data quality information, it shall be defined by one or more of these elements: ConceptualConsistency, DomainConsistency, FormatConsistency and TopologicalConsistency.

A data quality element shall refer to one measure only by one of the three following ways: a measure reference as defined in this standard, providing an identifier of a measure defined elsewhere, or providing the name and a short description of a measure.
If Metaquality is reported as data quality information, it should be defined by one or more of these elements: Confidence, Representativity and Homogeneity.

In addition to the descriptors provided for QualityElement, a reference to the related QualityElement shall be provided for Metaquality. NOTE The related quality element is the element on which the metaquality element applies.

If PositionalAccuracy is reported as data quality information, it shall be defined by one or more of these elements: AbsolutePositionalAccuracy, RelativePositionalAccuracy and GriddedDataPositionalAccuracy.
All quality elements shall have at least one QuantitativeResult, ConformanceResult, DescriptiveResult, or CoverageResult.
A conformance result shall be described with an expression of pass or fail against conformance quality levels and a citation to the data product specification or user requirements.
If evaluation has been performed against conformance levels originating from different sources, more than one data quality ConformanceResult may be provided for the same measure.
An identifier should be provided for the specification attribute of ConformanceResult. NOTE: specification is of type CI_Citation, in which, as defined by ISO 19115-1, the identifier is optional.

A coverage result shall contain at least a description of a resultContent in case when resultFile and resultFormat are not provided. Alternatively, a description of resultFile and resultFormat shall be provided in case resultContent is not provided.
A descriptive result shall be described with a textual expression of the result.
If TemporalQuality is reported as data quality information, it shall be defined as one or more of these elements: AccuracyOfTimeMeasurement, TemporalValidity and TemporalConsistency.

If ThematicQuality is reported as data quality information, it shall be defined as by one or more of these elements: ClassificationCorrectness, NonQuantitativeAttributeCorrectness and QuantitativeAttributeAccuracy.

A quantitative result shall be described with at least one value. If the value is expressed by number, the unit of measure shall be given. NOTE 1: Units of measure are defined in ISO 19103:2015, Clause C.4. In case, these lists are not exhaustive, they can be extended in compliance with ISO 19115-1, Annex C.
If the data quality differs between upper and lower level, then supplemental information should be provided at lower level.
Data quality shall be reported as metadata in compliance with Clause 8, Clause 11 and Annex C of this standard, and in compliance with ISO 19115-1:2014.
Direct evaluation methods (directInternal or directExternal) should be used in preference to indirect evaluations.
If an indirect evaluation method is reported, it shall be accompanied by a description on how it was determined, i.e. a value for deductiveSource shall be provided.
For a sample-based inspection samplingScheme, lotDescription and samplingRatio shall be defined.
When evaluated geographic dataset is heterogeneous and quality is specified for its individual parts, separate evaluation should be carried out for individual parts of the dataset.

When possible, measures defined in ISO 19157-3 shall be used in data quality evaluation and to represent the result of the quality evaluation in quality evaluation report and metadata. NOTE 1: If no measure as defined in ISO 19157-3 is applicable, additional, user defined measures can be used (see 9.3). NOTE 2: Elements defined in other standards (e.g. ISO/IEC 25000 series) can be used for extending the quality model, if applicable.

New quality measure shall be defined as a specialisation of QualityMeasure, or one of its subtypes (see Clause 9) according to the rules for metadata extensions (ISO 19115-1:2014, Annex C) and rules for domain profiles of standard schemas (ISO 19109:2015, Clause 8.3). For each new quality measure, a measure identification, a measure name, an elementName, a definition and a valueType shall be defined. If the quality measure is derived from a basic measure, the basic measure shall be referenced. If an item is adopted from an external source the reference to the external source shall be given. If a measure uses an auxiliary variable, a reference MeasureParameter shall be provided for the measure.

Whenever possible, a BasicMeasure should be used as the basis for defining a new quality measure. NOTE A variety of measures are based on counting of erroneous items. There are also several measures dealing with the uncertainty of numerical values. In order to avoid repetition, the most common methods of constructing count-related measures, as well as general statistical measures, for one- and two-dimensional random variables should be defined in terms of basic measures.
If a QualityMeasure is based on one of the basic measures, a BasicMeasure shall be described by its name, definition and valueType. NOTE The basic measures are defined in ISO 19157-3.
If a measure uses the concept of errors for reporting correct or incorrect items, description should contain an explanation of when item is classified as incorrect.
If a measure uses auxiliary variable, a MeasureParameter, defined by its name, definition and valueType shall be provided. More than one MeasureParameter may be provided for an auxiliary variable.
For any measure, which contains additional information in an external source, a reference to this external source shall be provided.
An optional standalone quality evaluation report shall not replace the metadata.

Where the result has been aggregated, a standalone quality evaluation report should be provided to complete the information provided in the metadata. This report includes fully detailed information on the original result (with measure(s) and evaluation procedure(s)), aggregated result and aggregation method.

When several quality results for different data quality elements are aggregated into a single result, this should be reported in metadata as a result of evaluation of a datasets conformance with the data product specification or user requirements. See D.4.1.4 for an example.
When aggregated result is reported in metadata a reference to the original quality evaluation results on individual element(s) shall be provided.

When several quality results for the same data quality element are aggregated into a single result of this element, the result should be reported in metadata as a result for this data quality element. See D.4.1.2 and D.4.1.3 for examples.
A standalone quality evaluation report detailing the source of derivation (e.g. quality results, derivation method) should be generated for a derived result.
Metadata on derived result should provide a reference to the standalone quality evaluation report and the original data quality result.
In case a standalone quality evaluation report exists for the reported data quality metadata, a reference to this report should be provided.
